 <p><font size=5 color="gray"><b>Wotan</b><font size=3> Shaman Elder of the <a href="http://www.talonguard.org/shanks"><font color="red">Shanks</font></a> <br>

<font size=2><b><i>It is better to have less thunder in the mouth and more lightning in the hand.  - Apache Proverb</font></font></font></i></b></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uiamwotan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>I am Wotan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.thegamevine.com/~Wotan_Rogue/yinyang.gif border=0 BORDER=0> at: 6/29/01 5:46:11 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon2.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulisboa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lisboa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/29/01 8:09:45 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Get on the record now for SZ ....</span><hr size=1> Highpass, if the evils play their cards right, will be the turning point in the game.  If the evils take it, something they haven't accomplished on any zek to my knowledge, they have an excellent central base for leveling up through 35, banking, binding, selling, even for their iksar members.  It is also the only way three races can go not KOS to Freeport and Qeynos.  It gives them access to the Karanas, to Runnyeye, and eventually into taking over western Antonica.  <br>
<br>
Mark my words, Highpass will be the Stalingrad of Norrath.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulegnavalsharess.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Legna ValSharess</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/29/01 9:12:43 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Get on the record now for SZ ....</span><hr size=1> I don't believe that evil is going to have quite the strangle hold that you think.<br>
<br>
Granted, there are some good evil players. However, most of their forces include the grief players, cowards, power kiting necros, and the portal campers from Rallos.<br>
<br>
Grief players are generally weak at pvp. They are good at being a nuisance, but I don't think they are any real weapon. They will get one kill, then have to run before they are destroyed by the others in the area.<br>
<br>
Cowards went evil because they heard it would be the best. They have little to no pvp skill, and don't understand tactics. They joined the pvp server because they knew they would be on the strong team and figure that gurantees they get easy wins.<br>
<br>
The kiters have never been good at pvp. Really don't need to go much further into that one.<br>
<br>
portal campers is what I call the weak pk. They don't do it to grief, they do it to disguise their own lack of ability. The 6 DB wizard ice comet portal guardians come to mind. If you run at them with anything from within the zone, they all evac/gate almost instantly. <br>
<br>
Evil will have the numbers. But numbers aren't going to be enough. You need skilled people. I expect to see a much higher skilled player ratio on the goods and neutral teams, as in general, the good players will go to the underdogs.<br>
<br>
-L <p>Legna
