55 Shadows
Rallos Zek</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukilii.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kilii</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/30/01 2:10:25 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Get on the record now for SZ ....</span><hr size=1> Interesting, I was thinking of branching over to Highhold very soon.  I have had the luxury of a lot of uninterrupted free time for the time being and have gotten to watch the teir'dal explosion.   East commons was in dark hands very early.  Many of the humans had gone dark and many half elven bards were evil too.   West commons was in neutral hands early on, it seems, but evil made a comeback and drove the pecks back to Kithikor group by group.  Our group suffered a setback early on when we were seperated from each other and got caught with our robes down, as it were.   After our defeat we killed many, many halflings in retribution.  And the funny thing is, they came to us.  Mostly.   Three out of four of our group were from Rallos, so pvp isn't new to us and we just pvp'd when folks came by where we were levelling or just outright attacked us.  I look forward to the scoring system starting at 20th.  That'll show who is walking the walk.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
